Package uk.co.strangeskies.mathematics.expression

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CloneDecouplingExpression<S extends CloneDecouplingExpression<S,T>,T extends Cloneable>
    Similar to CopyDecouplingExpression for Cloneable Expression types.
    CopyDecouplingExpression<S extends Expression<S,T>,T extends Copyable<T>>
    A basic interface extension of Expression providing a default implementation of CopyDecouplingExpression.decoupleValue() which simply copies the result of Expression.getValue().
    Expression<S extends Expression<S,T>,T>
    An expression for use in reactive programming.
    SelfExpression<S extends SelfExpression<S>>
    A variable for use in reactive programming.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BinaryExpression<S extends BinaryExpression<S,O1,O2,R>,O1,O2,R>
    As UnaryExpression, but with two operands.
    ConditionalExpression<O>
    An Expression whose primary dependency is conditional on a Boolean Expression dependency.
    DependentExpression<S extends Expression<S,T>,T>
    TODO
    ExpressionImpl<S extends Expression<S,T>,T>
    An abstract class to help designing mutable expression, implementing a simple observer list, locking mechanism, and update mechanism.
    IdentityExpression<T>
    An Expression based on the behaviour of the IdentityProperty class, with the lazy updating behaviour of LockingExpression for Observers.
    ImmutableExpression<S extends Expression<S,T>,T>
    An abstract class to help designing mutable expression, implementing a simple observer list, locking mechanism, and update mechanism.
    ImmutableReadLock
    A read lock over an immutable object.
    LockingExpression<S extends Expression<S,T>,T>
    An abstract class to help designing mutable expression, implementing a simple observer list, locking mechanism, and update mechanism.
    TrinaryExpression<S extends TrinaryExpression<S,O1,O2,O3,R>,O1,O2,O3,R>
    As UnaryExpression, but with three operands.
    UnaryExpression<S extends UnaryExpression<S,O,R>,O,R>
    An implementation of Expression with a single data dependency, whose value is derived through the application of a function to the value of that dependency.
